===Etymology===
; “in it; on it; here”
: From {{och-l|於|id=2}} + {{m|och||*-n|demonstrative suffix|sc=Latn}}, an element equivalent to {{zh-l|*之|him; her; it}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Pulleyblank, 1995}}). {{zh-ref|Smith, 2012}} identifies this latter element as {{och-l|是}}, with ''d'' canonicalized to ''n'' in coda. Compare {{och-l|爰}}.

; “where; how”
: Probably a variant of {{och-l|安|where; how}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

